Accounts API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

CheckAccountAssociationExistsByID
GET | Returns: int? | Path: /Accounts/AccountAssociation/Exists/ID/{ID}

Check if this ID exists and return the id if it does (null if it does not)

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ID int path Yes The identifier for the record to call.

TypeScript Example

var id: number = this.someValue1;
this.cvApi.accounts.CheckAccountAssociationExistsByID(id).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

UpdateAccount
PUT | Returns: CEFActionResponse<int> | Path: /Accounts/Account/Update

Use to update an existing account.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
IsTaxable bool? body No Whether the account can be charged Taxes for taxable products, optional, defaults to true when not set
TaxExemptionNo string body No The exemption certificate value
TaxEntityUseCode string body No Tax code for complete or partial exemptions
IsOnHold bool body No Account's On Hold status. Accounts on hold cannot complete purchases until this is turned off
Credit decimal? body No The amount of Credit this Account has available, optional
Token string body No The token for the account
SageID string body No The SAGE customer number
